SUMMARY:Science Saturday for kids at Spring Lake Regional Park
DESCRIPTION:Bring your junior scientists over to the Environmental Discovery Center to enjoy a kids-only\, interactive science hour. Set your inner engineer loose by using a variety of random items to build a mini boat. Test your vessel’s success by placing it in water\, adding “passengers” and seeing how well it floats! Adults can head out into Spring Lake Park to enjoy rejuvenating\, kid-free time in nature! Activities are ideal for kids ages 6-12. The cost is $10 for in-county residents and $12 for out-of-county attendees. For more information\, contact Kalen Roloff Geck at ParkPrograms@sonoma-county.org. Registration required. \nPlease bring your own water and snacks. We recommend participants dress in layers and bring a hat and sunscreen. Most programs will happen rain or shine\, but may be canceled during heavy rains\, heavy smoke\, or extreme temperatures. Accommodations will be made for visitors with disabilities upon advance request. Parking is $7 or free with a Regional Parks membership pass.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/science-saturday-for-kids-at-spring-lake-regional-park-5/
LOCATION:Environmental Discovery Center\, Spring Lake Regional Park\, 393 Violetti Rd\, Santa Rosa\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
GEO:38.4542;-122.649
