SUMMARY:Saturday in the Museum with Sondheim
DESCRIPTION:An afternoon celebrating the music of Stephen Sondheim\, performed by Frederick Hodges\, Rodney Jackson\, Jr.\, Ken Stegmiller and Jojo Thompson. They’ll be sharing some of Sondheim’s most memorable music from his many plays\, including Into the Woods\, Company\, A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum\, West Side Story\, A Little Night Music\, and Sweeney Todd.
