SUMMARY:Sonoma Police Report LIVE! A staged reading at Sonoma Community Center
DESCRIPTION:UPDATE: This event is completely SOLD OUT. We are maintaining a waitlist. If you would like to be contacted about cancellations\, please follow the link to join the waitlist. There will be NO TICKETS AT THE DOOR. Thank you for making this event a huge fundraising success for the Center. \nThe Sonoma Police Report Live show promises to be a very fun\, crazy\, kooky show about the history of Sonoma you won’t find in winery gift shops\, hotel brochures\, destination magazine ads\, or “Top 10 small towns to live in” lists. Join us for a raucous staged reading of excerpts from the hilarious book\, “Sonoma Police Report: funny\, odd tales from the Wine Country\,” and fun audience-involved games. \nGet ready to hear some of the funniest police reports and stories from locals\, from the 80’s\, 90’s\, and early 2000’s. Bring some local knowledge\, for you will be tested! If you are old school Sonoma\, you are sure to enjoy a trip down memory lane. If you are new to Sonoma\, you are guaranteed to hear some stories that will make you blush\, learn\nsome history you didn’t know\, and chuckle at the madness and revelry of old Sonoma. \nCome one\, come all. This promises to be more fun than Netflix\, more fun than watching a folk band at the Farmer’s Market\, and almost as much fun as a night in the City of Sonoma drunk tank! \nPlaywright/Director: Joshua Farrell\nCast: Joshua Farrel\, Joe Herrschaft\, Vanessa Rognlien\, Cat Smith\, and Molly Spencer\nFoley Artist/DJ: Ronny Joe Grooms \nAbout the Playwright: Joshua Farrell\nJoshua Farrell grew up two blocks from the Sonoma Community Center and electrocuted himself while playing a joke under the air hockey machine at the original Boy’s (and Girl’s) Club\, then located in room 111. He has performed 3 previous times at SCC. He performed David Sedaris’s The Santaland Diaries\, The Fantasticks\, and in a Charlie’s Angels skit when he was 8. He is an actor who has performed across the country in regional theaters\, as well as in numerous commercials\, tv shows\, and films. He received his M.F.A. from American Conservatory Theatre\, and is a hospitality nerd who currently serves as the Director of Learning and Development for The Ritz-Carlton and JW Marriott\, Los Angeles. In addition to his book\, The Sonoma Police Report\, he authored two hospitality-focused books\, “Counter Culture: An Essential Guide for Service” and “Serving Up Excellence: Creating Meaningful Dining Experiences through the Power of Connection.” \nURL:\nTickets: https://go.evvnt.com/3468485-0?pid=5514 \nPrice: General Admission: USD 25.00 \nCategory: Arts | Performing Arts | Theatre \nDate and Time: Saturday March 14\, 2026 at 7:00 pm to 9:00 pm \nVenue details: Sonoma Community Center\, 276 East Napa Street\, Sonoma\, California\, 95476\, United States
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/sonoma-police-report-live-a-staged-reading-at-sonoma-community-center/
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center\, 276 East Napa Street\, Sonoma\, 95476
CATEGORIES:Theater
GEO:38.2918;-122.453
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Sonoma Community Center 276 East Napa Street Sonoma 95476;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=276 East Napa Street:geo:-122.453,38.2918
END:VEVENT
